review_blob: I love this beer. Love Love Love. Ive had it on tap, in the bottle, and I even bought a keg one time. It never disappoints. Its like a stout but without the kick in the nuts. It reminds me of Magic Hat #9 in that it is simply pleasant to drink.

I love this beer. Its smokey, a bit sweet, a very full bodied.

 Unfortunately, you can only get in NY as far as I know.
this is just a pretty nasty beer. I dont know what would make it taste good. possibly some food... onion rings maybe?
Shared one with a friend this evening. I dont have a good beer vocabulary yet. It had an alcoholic smell and taste. A little strong for my palate, but my friend loved it. Definitely a fun one to try.
earthy, grass, hay, golden, hazy, medium sweetness, lightly bitter, lightly sour, light body, slick feel, lively,
beer_name: Top of the Hill Kenan Summer Lager
